{"id":29,"parent_id":0,"book_id":80,"content_id":1,"language_id":1,"display_order":29,"title":"Chapter 26: The People of Ammon","subtitle":"","short_title":"Chapter 26","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-26-the-people-of-ammon","content":[["div",{"id":"container","role":"main"},["div",{"type":"chapter","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-26-the-people-of-ammon"},[".heading",{"id":"head1","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-26-the-people-of-ammon.head1"},[".titleNumber","Chapter 26"],["h1","The People of Ammon"]],[".bodyBlock",[".image",{"id":"f1","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-26-the-people-of-ammon.f1"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_029_01.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p3","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-26-the-people-of-ammon.p3"},"The sons of Mosiah taught the gospel to the Lamanites. Thousands of Lamanites repented and joined the Church."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p4","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-26-the-people-of-ammon.p4"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/alma/23.4-5"},"Alma 23:4–5"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f2","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-26-the-people-of-ammon.f2"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_029_02.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p5","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-26-the-people-of-ammon.p5"},"Those Lamanites who joined the Church called themselves Anti-Nephi-Lehies, or the people of Ammon. They were good, hardworking people."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p6","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-26-the-people-of-ammon.p6"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/alma/23.17-18"},"Alma 23:17–18"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/alma/27.26"},"Alma 27:26"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f3","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-26-the-people-of-ammon.f3"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_029_03.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p7","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-26-the-people-of-ammon.p7"},"The Lamanites who did not repent were angry with the people of Ammon and prepared to fight them."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p8","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-26-the-people-of-ammon.p8"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/alma/24.1-2"},"Alma 24:1–2"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f4","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-26-the-people-of-ammon.f4"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_029_04.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p9","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-26-the-people-of-ammon.p9"},"The people of Ammon knew that the wicked Lamanites would come to kill them but decided not to fight back. They had repented of killing."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p10","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-26-the-people-of-ammon.p10"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/alma/24.5-6"},"Alma 24:5–6"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f5","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-26-the-people-of-ammon.f5"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_029_05.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p11","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-26-the-people-of-ammon.p11"},"They buried their weapons deep in the ground and promised God they would never kill again."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p12","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-26-the-people-of-ammon.p12"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/alma/24.17-18"},"Alma 24:17–18"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f6","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-26-the-people-of-ammon.f6"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_029_06.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p13","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-26-the-people-of-ammon.p13"},"When the wicked Lamanites came and began killing them, they bowed to the ground and prayed."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p14","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-26-the-people-of-ammon.p14"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/alma/24.21"},"Alma 24:21"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f7","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-26-the-people-of-ammon.f7"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_029_07.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p15","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-26-the-people-of-ammon.p15"},"Seeing that the people of Ammon would not fight back, many of the wicked Lamanites stopped killing them."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p16","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-26-the-people-of-ammon.p16"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/alma/24.23-24"},"Alma 24:23–24"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f8","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-26-the-people-of-ammon.f8"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_029_08.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p17","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-26-the-people-of-ammon.p17"},"The Lamanites were sorry that they had killed. They threw down their weapons and joined the people of Ammon. They would not fight anymore."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p18","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-26-the-people-of-ammon.p18"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/alma/24.24-27"},"Alma 24:24–27"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f9","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-26-the-people-of-ammon.f9"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_029_09.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p19","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-26-the-people-of-ammon.p19"},"More Lamanites came to kill the people of Ammon. They still would not fight back, and many were killed."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p20","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-26-the-people-of-ammon.p20"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/alma/27.2-3"},"Alma 27:2–3"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f10","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-26-the-people-of-ammon.f10"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_029_10.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p21","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-26-the-people-of-ammon.p21"},"Not wanting the people he loved to be destroyed, Ammon prayed for help. The Lord told him to take his people and leave the land."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p22","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-26-the-people-of-ammon.p22"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/alma/27.4-5,10-12"},"Alma 27:4–5, 10–12"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f11","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-26-the-people-of-ammon.f11"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_029_11.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p23","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-26-the-people-of-ammon.p23"},"The Nephites in Zarahemla gave Ammon and his people the land of Jershon and protected them. They became friends."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p24","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-26-the-people-of-ammon.p24"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/alma/27.22-23"},"Alma 27:22–23"]]]]]]]],"refs":null}
